shared_text:
Shrewsbury Hose Company #1
June 15 at 10:56 AM Â·

Well neighbors, here's the story. Apparently when I uploaded Part II of the SBS Graduation, I didn't include all of the graduates. I don't know what happened, but I missed about 7 or 8 graduates. Mr MacConnell gave me an incomplete as a grade on the project, but he allowed me to finish it for partial credit. There is also apparently another blemish in my "permanent record." So, my sincere apologies to everyone I missed.

Here is the amended video! I also included music that is royalty free, since Sony and Facebook decided that a small volunteer Fire Company using "Pomp and Circumstance" on a grammar school graduation slide show was an enormous threat to their stockholders.

Congratulations again to all!

shared_text:
Shrewsbury Hose Company #1
June 10 at 9:12 PM Â·

Small town traditions are important. And being a volunteer Firefighter in a small town allows one to participate in a lot of traditions. One of those traditions is the Shrewsbury Hose Companyâ€™s role in the 8th Grade Graduation from Shrewsbury Borough School. We run up to the school in the Fire Engines and we lead a parade around town after the ceremony to let everybody know that weâ€™re sending another group of kids on their way to make a difference!

This year that tradition got a little flopped around. Instead of leading a post-graduation parade, we drove Mr. MacConnell around town so he could deliver diplomas to several of the graduates. Itâ€™s been a crazy year, one that none of us will likely ever forget. But today was the day that we were able to keep one of our small town traditions alive, albeit a little differently.

Congratulations to the Shrewsbury Borough School Class of 2020! Go change the world!
